description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM FOR 3 YEARS DUE TO MEET THE NEEDS OF THE SERVICE &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Specialist Information Analyst (Reporting &amp; Standards and Development)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At BCU Health Board we believe that data helps save lives and improve outcomes for patients. Working with doctors and nurses to understand what matters for their patients the Information Department has developed analytics that help our clinicians make better decisions and improve their services. If you want to be part of something that helps improve patient care for you and your family then we have a vacancy that could be just what you are looking for.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As we continue on our journey to implement a single Patient Administration System (PAS) across the 3 areas of our Health Board we are looking to bolster our team with an additional post that can help us meet the complex challenge of moving from a legacy system, and transferring that patient data safely over to a new system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an experienced professional to undertake the role of Senior Development Analyst within our Development team. The post holder will be working on a major Patient Administration System migration project. The post will be predominantly involved with the data migration and associated quality and completeness checks for the project. Other relevant areas will include ensuring legacy developments aligned to the existing PAS are transitioned across and included in the wider Data Warehouse infrastructure. The post holder will be required to assess technical options for delivering various key information developments and ensuring that bespoke applications are suitably embedded into an enterprise wide solution that aligns with the strategic direction of travel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a full induction and training package, flexible working hours and good future career opportunities. Most of all we are proud of our fantastic team ethic with everyone pulling together to make a difference.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you think this is the opportunity you are looking for to progress your career and want to hear more about joining our friendly and welcoming team then please contact the following for more information.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 18/11/20&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NamePeter BurchamJob titleInformation Development ManagerEmail addressPeter.J.Burcham@wales.nhs.ukTelephone number03000 850581&lt;/p&gt;
